<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8873&amp;p=93661#p93661"><![CDATA[
Right, it seems like most games make a pass for each file they access since they can't buffer the whole side in memory. When they make you wait through two passes, flip, wait through a pass, flip back and wait through a final pass it's very aggravating. Games which load between scenery changes become infuriating when either dying or getting bumped off screen by an enemy triggers two sets of loading to get back to where you want to be (I think Dracula II is an offender). Also if you get a disk error you still have to wait for the pass to complete and sometimes wait through a second pass where the read is reattempted. Great games, miserable loading.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=20">kyuusaku</a> — Fri May 11, 2012 12:47 am</p><hr />
